S|Load Manifest — what Marcus loads per venture|\| File \| Novizio \| Hourbour \| yvon-dashboard \| When \| // \|------\|---------\|---------\|----------------\|------\| // \| `ses.md` \| ✅ \| ✅ \| ✅ \| Always — first read \| // \| `ctx.md` \| ✅ \| ✅ \| ✅ \| Always \| // \| `FEEDBACK.md` \| ✅ 🔴 always · 🟡 if relevant \| ✅ \| ✅ \| Always (🔴 minimum) \| // \| `BRAND.md` \| If: copy, mkt, cnt, brand dec \| ✅ same \| ✅ same \| On demand \| // \| `DESIGN.md` \| If: any UI, visual, component, asset work \| ✅ same \| ✅ same \| On demand \| // \| 
S|File Roles — one job per file|\| File \| Job \| NOT for \| // \|------\|-----\|---------\| // \| `ses.md` \| What happened, what's next, what's blocked \| Why decisions were made \| // \| `ctx.md` \| Why + when decisions were locked (strategic) \| Rolling state or rules \| // \| `FEEDBACK.md` \| Rules from errors/corrections — 🔴🟡🟢 tagged, dated \| Strategic decisions \| // \| `BRAND.md` \| Who this vtr is to the world \| Visual execution \| // \| `DESIGN.md` \| How this vtr looks in code and assets \| Brand positioning \|
S|Venture Switch Protocol (Marcus)|``` // Stark: "switch to [vtr]" //     ↓ // 1. Save current vtr state → ventures/[current]/ses.md // 2. Output vtr SWITCH marker in conversation (hard boundary) // 3. Load new vtr: ses.md + ctx.md + FEEDBACK.md // 4. Load BRAND.md / DESIGN.md only if task requires it // 5. Re-read each agt's Quick ctx row for the new vtr // 6. ENGAGE: "Switching to [vtr]. Last active [date]. [In Flight task]. Continue or new task?" // ``` // **For deep UI or brand work: recommend new ses.** Structural isolation 
S|Cross-Venture Rules|Rules that apply across all ventures live in: // - `docs/mem/feedback.md` — agt behaviour, routing, self-improvement rules // - `docs/mem/design.md` — shared UI/design patterns across all ventures // Never put a cross-vtr rule inside a vtr file.